						<persName xml:lang="fa">خوزانى  اصفهانى، فضلى بيگ</persName>
					</author>
					<note>
						<label>Note concerning author: </label>Faz̤lī is the author of <title>Afz̤al al-Tavārīkh</title>. Charles Melville found that work was related to Iskandar Beg Munshi's work of this title: <title>Taʾrīkh ʿĀlam-ārā-yi 'Abbasi</title>. See his discovery in Christ's College library Dd.5.6: <ref target="http://www.ifao.egnet.net/bcai/31/30/">http://www.ifao.egnet.net/bcai/31/30/</ref>. See also Melville's "A lost source for the reign of Shah 'Abbas: The Afzal al-tawarikh of Fazli Khuzani Isfahani" on JSTOR: <ref target="https://www.jstor.org/stable/4311148">https://www.jstor.org/stable/4311148</ref>. Could this be yet another manuscript mixing the two works?!
					</note>
					<title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20883" change="#ids-cleanup">Taʾrīkh ʿĀlam-ārā</title><title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20883" change="#ids-cleanup"> Afz̤al al-Tavārīkh</title> 
